Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

After bumping GTSAM 4.1.1 to 4.2 the test target failed to build:
  testTracker.cpp:691: reference to 'Tracker' is ambiguous
plus cascading errors in testOpticalFlowPredictor.cpp.

Root cause: testTracker.cpp does `using namespace cv;` and
`using namespace VIO;` together, and the GTSAM 4.2 header chain
exposes another 'Tracker' (cv::Tracker via tracking module) at the
unqualified scope, making the bare name ambiguous.

testTracker.cpp:
- Qualify every bare 'Tracker' as 'VIO::Tracker' (10 occurrences:
  member type aliases, constructors, static helper calls).

testOpticalFlowPredictor.cpp:
- Add '#include <opencv2/viz.hpp>' so cv::viz::Color and
  cv::viz::Viz3d are visible (same root cause as the production
  fixes from the prior commit on this branch — opencv2/opencv.hpp
  doesn't transitively pull viz on Ubuntu 22.04 OpenCV 4.5.4).

testKimeraVIO now builds with -DKIMERA_BUILD_TESTS=ON. Many tests pass
under xvfb-run; one suite (LCDFixture) crashes on a missing vocab/data
fixture path — runtime data issue, out of scope for the compile fix.

